-- Euro-Area Construction Output Fell in September on Italy, France
-- B y   P a t r i c k   H e n r y
-- 2012-11-19T10:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-19/euro-area-construction-output-fell-in-september-on-italy-france.html
Euro-area  construction output  fell
in September as declines in  Italy , France and Spain offset
growth in Germany.  Construction in the 17-nation euro area dropped 1.4 percent
from August, when it rose a revised 0.6 percent, the European
Union’s statistics office in Luxembourg said today. From a year
earlier, construction  output  declined 2.6 percent.  While Germany, Europe’s largest economy, reported a gain in
construction output of 2.7 percent from August, Italian
production plummeted 8 percent in the month, according to
today’s report. France and Spain had declines of 0.5 percent and
0.2 percent, respectively. Ireland and Greece are not required
to provide monthly data.  In the 27-nation EU, output dropped 1.8 percent from
August, when it rose 0.2 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
